cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach to improve the performance of solving Mixed Integer Programming (MIP) problems. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves representing MIP instances as graphs and using Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN) to predict solution values, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which could place it in the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning to improve optimization performance could also place it in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
